This paper is primarily focused on image denoising, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also heavily utilizes deep neural networks for both noise estimation and image denoising, which suggests that it could also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of generative models, which could potentially place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper also discusses the estimation and removal of non-i.i.d. noise, which could potentially place it under the information theory (cs.IT) category.
